Overview
The Assistant Manager on NBC Sports social media team is a point person for day-to-day oversight of the entire NBC Sports portfolio. The ideal candidate will help us in growing our social business, and carries an authentic passion for digital media and sports with initiative to join a creative and collaborative environment.
Loving sports is great, but loving the intersection of social media, technology, sports and pop culture is even more important.
While the Assistant Manager role will focus broadly on our entire social portfolio, the role will have a special focus on our Sunday Night Football and flagship NBC Sports accounts. It is a full-time position that can be remotely based.

* Own the day-to-day content creation and community management of our Sunday Night Football and NBC Sports flagship accounts on all social platforms
* Oversee the short and long-term content workflow and management for the portfolio of NBC Sports social brands
* Develop and maintain the year-round Sunday Night Football and NBC Sports sections of the social content calendar
* Assist social media leadership in setting priorities and allocating appropriate resources toward NBC Sportsâ-trade; company-wide priority events
* Lead and participate in in ideation and brainstorming of creative and promotional content for both owned and earned social media
* Collaborate with various parts of the larger NBC Sports team, including production, talent, consumer engagement and sales on cross-company efforts
* Distill and analyze trends and social data to advance the efficiency of social content

